<TITLE> Another Faridpur road crash kills 3 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Faridpur, January 2 (bdnews24.com)  Three people were killed and thirteen injured when a private bus collided with an oil tanker on the Dhaka-Khulna highway on Saturday. The accident comes just a day after 17 bus passengers were killed in a crash on the same highway in Faridpur. Faridpur deputy commissioner Helaluddin Ahmed said Saturday's accident occurred at Digholia in Modhukhali Upazila at around 10:30am, as the bus belonging to Faridpur Sugar Mill hit the Padma Oil Company tanker head-on. The dead were identified as Helal Joardar, a book keeper of the sugar company, bus driver Tota Mia and an Ansar member. The bus was carrying Tk 3.5 lakh for sugarcane purchases, of which Tk 1.2 lakh was recovered immediately after the accident, Ahmed told bdnews24.com. Also, 70 rounds of bullets belonging to Ansar members on the bus were missing. Ahmed said 12 Ansars were guarding the cash on board the sugar mill vehicle. bdn
